      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/3/4970",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَبُو عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : \"اَلنَّظْرَةُ بَعْدَ اَلنَّظْرَةِ تَزْرَعُ فِي اَلْقَلْبِ اَلشَّهْوَةَ وَ كَفَى بِهَا لِصَاحِبِهَا فِتْنَةً\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4970 - It is narrated by Ibn Abi Umair from Al-Kahili who said that Abu Abdullah (as) said:\n\"A second glance after the first plants desire in the heart, and that is sufficient as a trial for its beholder.\""
        ]
      }
